@gvanrossum 
> Should we allow the example where a subclass overrides a field with a different type?

I think we should allow whatever is allowed by mypy.

This is not a good idea as you would break encapsulation. 

The recommended way (see Angular doc website) to share data through components is to use service.

If you still want to use scope/binding to share data you can create a directive to put inside table to communicate with the external world.

```Javascript
app.directive('stBinding',function(){
    return {
        require:'^stTable',
        scope:{
           //define binding here... cautious the table may not sync if you decide to set yourself some data whitout going through table.api => better being readonly 
           table:'='
        },
        link:function(scope,elem,  attr, table){
             scope.table = table
        }
    };
});
```

